    "client_msg_id": "0b6df72c-84fe-416e-9380-5a2fd5c51b7c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The scheduler is global.  The tempo is actually tied into whatever Ableton Link requests, but yeah, it's a simple thread which wakes up at regular intervals and provides tick events to the system.  Everything is using the same timeline, regardless of which component it is.\nWhat I'm _not_ doing yet, is scheduling new Ixi patterns to start at the first beat of the bar; but that should be simple enough - Thor says that's what he does for alignment.",
